This paper is primarily focused on the security and privacy aspects of a database system, making it a strong candidate for the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) category. Additionally, the paper discusses the functionality and features of the database, such as search and query capabilities, which aligns with the cs.DB (Databases) category. The paper also touches on topics related to cyber security (cs.CY), system infrastructure (cs.SI), and distributed computing (cs.DC), which are all relevant to the design and implementation of a secure database system.
